.TH "snd_hdac_acomp_register_notifier" 9 "snd_hdac_acomp_register_notifier" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hdac_acomp_register_notifier \- Register audio component ops
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hdac_acomp_register_notifier
.BI "(struct hdac_bus *bus "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_audio_component_audio_ops *aops "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
HDA core bus
.IP "aops" 12
audio component ops
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is supposed to be used only by a HD-audio controller
driver that needs the interaction with graphics driver.

This function sets the given ops to be called by the graphics driver.

Returns zero for success or a negative error code.
